20/07/2003
ZAGREB, Croatia -- Visiting Macedonian President Boris Trajkovski wrapped up three days of talks on Saturday (19 July) and reportedly said he hopes his country can follow Croatia's lead in implementing military reforms necessary to meet NATO standards. Defence Minister Zeljka Antunovic, who met with Trajkovski, spoke highly of Macedonia's efforts to step up Euro-Atlantic integration. Praising bilateral relations, Croatian President Stipe Mesic said there are no open issues between Macedonia and Croatia. (HINA, BBC - 19/07/03)
